messages.content: ImagesGrid is a plugin for ComfyUI that allows users to create simple grids of images with various settings.
What type of image grids can be created using ImagesGrid plugin?
Users can create simple grids of images and XYZPlot type grids (similar to auto1111) with more settings using the ImagesGrid plugin.
Does ImagesGrid plugin integrate with any other tools?
Yes, ImagesGrid plugin integrates with the efficiency custom node for ComfyUI.
Where can I find example workflows for the ImagesGrid plugin?
Example workflows for the ImagesGrid plugin can be found in the workflows directory of the GitHub repository: https://github.com/LEv145/images-grid-comfy-plugin/tree/main/workflows
How can I install the ImagesGrid plugin for ComfyUI?

To install the ImagesGrid plugin, download the latest stable release from https://github.com/LEv145/images-grid-comfy-plugin/archive/refs/heads/main.zip and unpack the node to the custom_nodes directory, for example in a folder named custom_nodes/ImagesGrid/.
Is the ImagesGrid plugin an open source project?
Yes, the ImagesGrid plugin is an open source project and its source code can be found on GitHub at https://github.com/LEv145/images-grid-comfy-plugin.
Who is the author of the ImagesGrid plugin for ComfyUI?
The ImagesGrid plugin for ComfyUI is developed by LEv145 on GitHub.
